HEADWORD: Gibbartas
<hw>Gib*bar"tas</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Ar.
<ets>jebb⟦amac⟧r</ets> giant; or L. <ets>gibber</ets> humpbacked: cf. F.
<ets>gibbar</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of several finback
whales of the North Atlantic; -- called also <altname>Jupiter
whale</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>jubartas</asp>,
<asp>gubertas</asp>, <asp>dubertus</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

